# .cursorrules — InnoTech Systems

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS v4 (config via app/globals.css @theme — no tailwind.config.ts)
- Framer Motion (all animations)
- Lucide React (icons only — no other icon libraries)
- shadcn/ui (Radix UI based)

## Design Rules
- Dark theme only. Base background is #070c18. Never use white or light backgrounds.
- Three fonts only: Chakra Petch (headings and H1–H4 only), DM Sans (body copy, nav links, buttons, labels), IBM Plex Mono (mono metadata, tags, slugs only).
- Never use Inter, Roboto, Arial, or system fonts anywhere.
- Nav link labels use DM Sans — NOT Chakra Petch. Chakra Petch is for headings only.
- All colours must reference CSS variable tokens — no raw hex values in components or pages.
- Icon stroke width is always 1.5 — never use the default 2.
- No looping animations. No parallax. No autoplay video unless muted.
- Animation durations: hover 150ms, dropdowns/menus 200ms, section reveals 300–400ms.
- One primary CTA per section maximum.
- Cards use 3px left-border accents — never full coloured card backgrounds.
- Max body copy column width: 680px.
- All page sections must be wrapped in a max-width container (max-w-screen-xl or max-w-7xl) centred with mx-auto and horizontal padding px-6 or px-8.

## Component Conventions
- All client components must have "use client" at the top.
- Framer Motion variants defined outside the component, not inline.
- No magic numbers — use spacing and colour tokens only.
- Mobile-first. Base styles for mobile, enhance at lg breakpoint.
- Footer must always be full-width background with inner content wrapped in max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 or px-8.

## Naming — Always Use These Exact Terms
- Product 1: SafeGuard
- Product 2: AutoLock
- Product 3: RADARLink
- Never: "automated charging" — always "autonomous charging"
- Never: "Congreagate" — always "Congregate Detection"
- Never: "Minning" — always "Mining"
- Never: "Our Company" in nav — always "Company"
- Never: "Overnight Charge Facility" — always "Charge Depot"
